  "commentary": "With SPX at 7087 sitting just below the 7089 GEX flip, dealers are in a PIN regime where they're long gamma and providing stabilizing flow - they'll be buying this dip toward the 7065 negative gamma wall while selling any push back above 7089. The massive positive gamma walls at 7100 (+4.9B) and 7200 (+7.3B) should act as strong magnets, with dealers increasingly selling rallies as price approaches these levels. Key levels to watch are the 7089 flip (regime change), 7065 downside support where dealer buying accelerates, and the 7100-7200 corridor where positive gamma concentration creates a high-probability mean reversion zone.\n\nBottom line: expect the market to get pulled back toward 7100 with limited downside below 7065.",
